reviews.text: they served dishes real fresh

After reading the name Golden Shangai Cuisine, I was expecting to be blown away by the Chinese cuisine. However, the microwave meals served to us were very dissapointing. A happy meal from Mac Donalds has more taste. 

The staff was a bit rude and uses pushy sales methods. 

By the way. The restaurant has no toilet and charges you for peanuts, even if you didn’t order them. 

I would search for another place. Don’t waste your dollars here.
taste fair

Happy hours  menu available everyday including weekends and public holidays  from 14:30  to 16:00。Spend less than HK$200.- including all time refills tea and service charge for two persons.

result.name: 金滬庭京川滬菜館 - 東涌

reviews.text: 從東薈城outlet三樓往海堤映灣園方向步行約3分鐘，經過名店區便可到達，位置不是最方便，樓下有Starbucks，Teawood；開店已有10年，屬中價食肆，是區內有名之上海餐廳，有固定捧場客人。
不錯，保持水準
東涌區唯一食上海菜的食肆，平日晚上不爆場，三五知己傾計好地方。埋單三人港幣625元
侍应悠手好閑沒在意，完全不合本地人口味，菜式大开大埋沒有精緻的观念，價錢又贵，十分失望！
衛生極差！有曱甴侍應都當無事發生！

result.name: Citygate Outlets

reviews.text:
Calling City Gate an Upscale Outlet Mall sounds like an oxymoron. That's exactly what it is.
A nice mall with many shops selling last season products, however bargains though possible are hard to find.
Large areas have closed for refurbishment, good selection of shops however prices are not that cheap like most outlet shopping.
The mall was not bad.  However, the shops were mainly designer brands. And they are targeting mainland China visitors.   It can get pretty crowded in weekends.

Lots of shops...and more shops.
Taste supermarket is great...well stocked with 'international' goodies.
Lots of options for lunch or a quick snack.
You can check out cheap stuff there easily
